OL,3,CVillagers say wet weather has left
OL,4,Cswarms of midges plaguing their homes
OL,6,F"This year we've had the perfect storm
OL,7,Ffor midge abundance, in that we've had
OL,8,Fa very mild winter, followed by an
OL,9,Fincredibly wet spring, so those two
OL,10,Fthings together means that there's a
OL,11,Flocal explosion of midges, though it's
OL,12,Fnot necessarily a bad thing."
OL,14,F"On slightly warmer days, or on days
OL,15,Fwhere there is less wind, there may be
OL,16,Fgreater concentrations of them.
OL,18,F"It can be a nuisance in the morning
OL,19,Fwhen you're walking the dog, but no
OL,20,Fserious damage."
